The best MSS. of de Finibus are: A, Palatinus I, llth c., which ends soon after the beginning of Book IV; Β, Palatinus ΙΙ; and E, Erlangensis, 15th c. These three form one family, within which B and E are more closely related. The other MSS. known to Madvig form a second family, inferior in general to the former, though, as Miiller points out, not to be entirely dispensed with. Both families according to Madvig descend from a late and already consider- ably corrupted archetype.
